        <div class="source" style=" ">
            <ol class="text"><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You stride out from your ship, sands of the wasteland beneath your boots</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Scanning the landscape, all you see is a depressing sea of dust</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You detected artificial radio signals not far from here, you landed in hopes of encountering a native creature in a secluded area</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You follow the signals toward the source. The sights along the way fit the theme of this dead world</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Dust, dust and more dust. Occasionally broken by the odd dead plant or half buried steel girder</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You wonder why the Senate gave you this star system, the only life sustaining planet nuked itself to oblivion</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Though, this place was uncharted, and as the best Vanguard in his class, it was your job to discover this information</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You took the time to read some info from the sensors in your armor</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Atmosphere is 79% N2, 19% O2, 0.5% CO2 and 0.5% trace gasses, primarily 106^I and 60^Co</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The air was breatable, and the radionuclotides confirm your suspition of a mass nuclear exchange</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Honestly, that makes your job easier. You could probably conquer this place before a crusade fleet arrives</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Up ahead, you spot a small ruin that juts out the landscape</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You wander up towards it, you might gleam something from it, or just break the monotony</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Along the way, suddenly a loud *CRACK* has you ducking down</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;*CRACK* *CRACK* *CRACK* three gunshots follow, you immediately run for the ruins</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You slid to cover and pull out the pistol in its thigh holster</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You peer out from a window, two immaciated creatures run from a boulder. The sand colored creatures wear makeshift armor</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;One holds out what seems to be a pistol and fires two shots, while the other runs towards a target out of view with a crude axe</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The pistolier covers their teammate as they charge toward much louder gunshots</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;*CRACK* The pistolier takes a bullet to the neck and a cloud of blue-green liquid sprays out</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The barbarian runs through a hail of fire to grab the pistol, and it squeezes two rounds at the unseen target</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You hear a muffled grunt and a &quot;Ni&#039;Tar!&quot; eminate from where the gunshots came from while barbarian cranes his neck to see if the other is moving</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You move your foot slightly, which causes a pile of rubble to topple over</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The sound catches the attention of the barbarian, who raises the pistol as it slowly moves toward the ruin</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You aim your pistol through the window corner and squeeze off a textbook mozambique drill</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Barbarian drops down dead, bleeding out the blue-green fluid seen before</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You look out to see any other threats that might be there.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The coast is clear, you move towards the bodies in the dirt</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;They&#039;re rather strange, the creatures are bipedal, but they have digitigrade legs </div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;A sand colored fur covered the body, thought these ones were rather patchy</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;They resembled a blend of human and desert fox</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You shake your head in disgust at the thought</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Their patchwork outfits indicate they&#039;re not high on the hirearcy or have many resources</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You contemplate imprinting the one with the intact head, but a loud grunting grabs your attention</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You find your way to its source, pistol at the ready. A much more well equiped and fed creature lies fatally wounded, slumped against a boulder</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;It wears more uniform armor (not that it did it much good) above a white, shining and honeycombed jumpsuit</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;A battle rifle lies beside it, probably what it was shooting it.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The creature looks up at you, its eyes go wide but is on its last legs</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You&#039;re sure this one has the info you seek. You sit on the creature&#039;s chest and pull off your helmet</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The creature meekly resists, but the blood loss stops any real force</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Looking the enemy in the eye, you drive a spike into the brainstem</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The creature trembles and foams at the mouth as the pack does its work</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You&#039;re bombarded by memories of the guard as he shutters last, brain completely destroyed</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;He was a caravan guard who was ambushed by raiders on his way to Inara, a prosperous city nearby</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You even see what he saw as you subdued and imprinted him</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You take a skin and blood sample and put them in the containers</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You strip him of his equipment. Armor, rifle, even the jumpsuit (luckily, he was your size)</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You radio to your parked ship</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;Sunny, I&#039;ve got samples and imprinted one of the natives. Get the cruiser ready and deploy the disguse maker!&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;Okay!&quot; A cheery voice crackles in your ear</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You knew none of that would be done when you got back</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You glance back at the ruins you hid in, only to shrug and turn away</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You trek back towards the cruiser for about 15 minutes to find machines strewn about, one of them even was the bioprinter</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Honestly impressed she did more or less what you said, you plug in the bioprinter</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;It asks for a sample and you oblige with the samples from the guard</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You sketch a disguise from pics and videos of the &#039;Padmayans&#039; as they call themselves</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The time of printing is about 2 hours, you take the time to copy the jumpsuit to make one for you and Sunny</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You call her from looking in the cargo area for Gods know what and inspect her</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;She pops out her head and throws a wrench to the ground</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You look her over, sand colored fur, small sandy mane, and her fox-like build makes her look like one of their cubs</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;Well, Fortuna conspires to aid us. You look like a padmayan child, so I&#039;m gonna give you a jumpsuit and call it at that.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;Ooohhh...&quot; Sunny glares at the jumpsuit printing on the metal plate &quot;I really like the shineyness&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;Sunny, pack up the mess you&#039;ve made and we&#039;ll find a place to set up a F.O.B.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;She stands at attention with a salute, then rushes over to do exactly what you don&#039;t want to happen</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;She&#039;s sweet, but you get the feeling the Vanguard board was fucking with you when they dumped her pod in your lap and said she was &#039;advanced&#039;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;She throws equipment in haphazardly, the crashing sounds become a background noise as you plan your next move</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Inara, the city closest to here seems a good place to get information about the current state of affairs</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You decide an aireal view would be the best move</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You were packed up enough to leave, no time to waste</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Climbing into the cockpit, you motion Sunny over to get in. She scurries up the wing</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;All the preflight checks were irrelevant for your skill at piloting</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You shortly roll into the air, kicking up dust along the way</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You peer out the window to search for any of the landmarks you&#039;ve seen in the guard&#039;s memories</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You were comfortably high up to not be seen, the lidar and flir don&#039;t see anything</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;It&#039;s been a while, the sun&#039;s gone down and darkness engulfs the landscape</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You roll left to look down, to find a sea of soft lights amid the darkness</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You distinctly remember a large, monolithic tower near the center. Its light peers out like the Pharos</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Another issue was where to set up. Lidar scanned the area, the city was on the side of a much larger ruin</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;A charred skyscraper caught your attention. It was within the city walls, a large hole that the crusier could fit</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Most of all, the FLIR didn&#039;t see any form of occupation. </div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;Here, this is our F.O.B.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You gently fly into the wide hole on the ruin side, just below the top floor</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The loud scraping noises did not detract from your perfect landing, the engines quit</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Emerging from the cockpit, you slowly clear the lower levels, looking for a good place to set up</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The second floor down from the new hangar looked to be good</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You open the cargo hatch, equipment falling all around to reveal the now finished bio printer</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You reach for the disguise and examine the face mask, the frame holds up the muzzle and should articulate the way these &#039;Padmayans&#039; would</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You strip out of your armor and try on the skinsuit, the biomesh sticks perfectly</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Then you place the face mask on, it sticks to everything perfectly</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You put on the jumpsuit over it, you felt the nylon material across your fur. Once again, the biosuit works perfectly</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Looking into a mirror, you check the articulation of the face, ears and tail. Angry; teeth out, ears back and tail raised</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Happy; ears perked up, black lipped smile and curled up tail</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;A few other tests of the articulation and this suit could fool even you</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;A sinister smile crept across your face, and you spoke in the Padmayan tongue</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;&lt;Face of the enemy&gt;&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You turn to call Sunny over to look at you, She didn&#039;t take to that very well</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;Where did you go? Where is he?&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;I&#039;m right here, this is my guise. And be quiet, do you want to wake the neighborhood?&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;Maybe.&quot; Sunny tilted her head</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Tapping your foot, you remember Sunny&#039;s jumpsuit draping over the side</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;Try this on, you&#039;ll be going as my little sister. This is what the natives wear.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;Okay!&quot; Sunny takes to it rather excitedly. You move to the other side of the cruiser to give her some privacy as she changes</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You turn to the next issue, setting up camp. Moving the heavy prefab is gonna be a pain.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;A large sheet of metal catches your attention, you could slide it down the stairs to the floor below</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;Surprise!&quot; Sunny jumps out in her new jumpsuit, scaring the shit out of you</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;Don&#039;t do that!&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You lean on the cruiser as you catch your breath</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;Well, not that you&#039;re done. We&#039;re gonna set up camp for tonight.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You grab the sheet metal and drag it to the cargo hatch. Sunny tips the prefab out of the hatch while you catch it</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The damned thing weighs a tonne, you lower the crate onto the sheet, your back about to give out</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;Sunny, come on. We got to push this thing to the stairs, we&#039;ll slide it down and set it up there.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The two of you push against the prefab crate. It&#039;s a demanding task despite the genetic and cybernetic augmented strength</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You reach the stairs, and lay out the plan for the stairs.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;Alright, You push the thing over the stairs and I&#039;ll control its sliding on the other side.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You move to the stair side and put your hands on the crate, Sunny pushes the thing over the top stair</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;It starts sliding, and you struggle to keep it from running you down.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The crate starts sliding off the sheet metal, you try your best to keep it on, but it catches on a stair near the bottom</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The crate tips over and the full weight falls on your shoulders. With a quick breath, you let it rotate down and land on the floor. </div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;Alright, we&#039;ll do that again and set up on the lower floor. Grab that sheet, and we&#039;ll roll it on top.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Sunny tips the thing over onto the sheet metal, and the process repeats.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;After another time of nearly nearly being crushed be the prefab, the two of you manage to set the prefab in position.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;Now, for the grand opening...&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You pull out the pin, and the crate pops open. Walls emerge and solidify, the braces lock up properly, everything looks good</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The loud thumping noises no longer concern you, the natives don&#039;t care or can&#039;t hear</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The two of you walk inside, you look to find the bare bones furniture set themselves up</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Beds, collapsing library and the grid controller.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You inspect the grid controller, the prefab is working normally. Temperature and atmosphere normal.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You decide to not activate the fuel cell, it would just waste power</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;Sunny, we&#039;ll call it a night and set up later tomorrow.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;She agreed and climbed up the upper bunk</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You changed out the skinsuit and hang it in the life support bag, you put on your casual wear</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The exhaustion of the day&#039;s events caught up with you, you flop onto the bottom bunk</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Tomorrows plans causally pass your thoughts, take a stroll through town and find some form of information repository</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You&#039;re soon out like a light</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The first thing you feel in the morning is something warm and furry crushing your face. A loud snoring emitted from the culprit</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;Sunny. Can you please get off my face?&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The snoring continued, and so you pull you arms free to put the furry mass on the floor</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;H-huh? W-wha...?&quot; Sunny looks around, dazed and confused. You simply put on your disguise and ready for the day</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Sunny had slept in her jumpsuit, and had started combing her sand colored mane with a wire combed plug</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You didn&#039;t have the will to stop it, so you just briefed her on today&#039;s plan</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;We&#039;re gonna head out into town and find out what we can about the area, just act like you belong and we&#039;ll be fine.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Sunny was half paying attention, you just gave up on trying to maintain discipline</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Disguise ready and Sunny ready to go, you place a few LRAD pads along the stairwell to deter any intruders.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You check around the charred doorway to look for any witnesses, but you&#039;re clear</div></li><li class="li1"><div 