7&#039; persisted. Maybe it would hold the secrets to their remaining technology and hopefully reveal some form of weakness for you to exploit</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;And perhaps, there may still be missiles ready to fire in their silos, a lovely treat of irony from their forebearers </div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Still, that one girl may be a problem. She seems more clever than most, best to eliminate her</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Your plotting ends when the class ended. The others walked out of the room and you followed suit</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Once outside, you heard a familiar voice call your name from the bottom of the stairs &lt;&quot;Galecthay!&quot;&gt; The black haired girl called out, as you turned to meet her</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You size her up as she walked towards you</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Her jet black mane was worn in a much more human style down to her shoulders. She wore the white, honeycombed jumpsuit that ran from her neck to just above the knees and elbows that the others wore, and she filled it out very well...</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You scrub that thought out. Yellow iris&#039;d eyes stare daggers at you as she approaches. No one believes her, play it cool</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&lt;&quot;Ah, It&#039;s you. I failed to catch your name ms.?&quot;&gt;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&lt;&quot;Na&#039;Rasha, and let me say this. You may have the others fooled, but i understand your nature. And I&#039;m gonna bring it to light as I drag your body through the street.&quot;&gt;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&lt;&quot;And I&#039;m gonna be king of all Ara, live in a big shiny house and drink non-radioactive water. Besides, I fail to see how you&#039;d accomplish that.&quot;&gt;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Na&#039;