ny repairs.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&quot;It&#039;s a small issue, the council wanted to keep it quiet so people don&#039;t start freaking out.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Roll for persuasion</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;They look at each other, then shrugged. &quot;All right, you&#039;re good.&quot; They stepped aside</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Fortuna smiles upon you this day. You look at the control panel, a slot the size of a playing card sat next to a switch and below three lights</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You try the badge, then turn the key. The door begins sliding open into a dark, musty interior</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;A malevolent smile creeps across the muzzle on your face-mask</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;The blaring of the open access alarms echo through the office, catching Na&#039;Rasha&#039;s attention</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;She walked across Ravoi&#039;s desk, the head commerce organizer walks in with bottle in hand.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;Ah good, that glorified mechanic finally got off his ass and does his job.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;Didn&#039;t Edom storm off towards the apartments on the south side?&quot; She inquired</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;He probably made a round about way to his job.&quot; Ravoi took another sip</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;He looked smaller than normal, and the fact no one notified the guards.&quot; Na&#039;Rasha was getting a bit suspicious</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;Granted, they&#039;re smarter than the average caravan thug, better make your money sink count.&quot;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;&quot;None of the proper procedure